Black Mulberry trees from China were imported to Virginia by Lucas Vasquez de Alyon in 1525 or 1526 to feed silk worms. Did the Powhatan nearly bring a premature end to Jamestown when the Pamaunke gave large suplies of those berries (perhaps plump but still red, thus unripe)? I have read that birds eating these unripe berries flew into trees. Could this have been why John Smith found the men left at the fort, acting as he described, when he returned in 1608? Could that be why he later set his powder pouch on fire and had trouble with other leaders of Jamestown?